Downloading and Processing Data

Yujin Choi

2023-02-28

I. Project Hypothesis and Details

Hypothesis: Genes differentially expressed across old populations have significant overlap with HGPS compared to the young population. [1]

Dataset: RNA-seq data of fibroblast cell lines of a wide-range of ages as well as from HGPS patients. [GEO] [SRA]

  • 10 samples (<10yo), 10 samples (>80yo), 10 samples (HGPS)

Technical Problems: Some of these reads are done through different Illumina sequencing platforms (HiSeq 2500 and NextSeq 500) which potentially can cause variability. There are no technical replicants between these two platforms. There might also be biases in the data as most of the samples are Caucasian and also samples are from different skin locations.

Additional Information:

  • Data generated by Salk Institute for Biological Studies [1] [GEO] [SRA]
  • Human dermal fibroblasts with three conditions: young (<10yo), old (>80yo), and HGPS patients.
  • Used Illumina TruSeq Stranded mRNA kit which uses Poly-A selection
  • Single-end Stranded RNA-Seq; read lengths usually 75 bp, but a few are 51 bp
  • The paper aligned to HG19 Human Genome with STAR but I will alighn to HG38

IV. Build Index and Align Sample

Used a bash script to index the reference genome with STAR with the parameter set to --sjdbOverhang 74.

#!/bin/bash -l
#SBATCH --partition=angsd_class
#SBATCH --nodes=1
#SBATCH --ntasks=1
#SBATCH --job-name="genome_index"
#SBATCH --time=10:0:00 # HH/MM/SS
#SBATCH --mem=50G # memory requested, units available: K,M,G,T
#SBATCH --mail-user=yuc4017@med.cornell.edu
#SBATCH --mail-type=ALL
#SBATCH --requeue

mamba activate angsd

STAR --runMode genomeGenerate --runThreadN 1 \
        --genomeDir /athena/angsd/scratch/yuc4017/genome/index \
        --genomeFastaFiles /athena/angsd/scratch/yuc4017/genome/Homo_sapiens.GRCh38.dna_sm.primary_assembly.fa \
        --sjdbGTFfile /athena/angsd/scratch/yuc4017/genome/Homo_sapiens.GRCh38.109.gtf \
        --sjdbOverhang 74

Used a bash script to fastqc the reads of sample SRR7093809.fastq.gz. The fastqc results show that the quality of the reads are fairly good as seen in Figure 1 below. There are no adapter contaminations either. Then, aligned with STAR to the reference genome. samtools is used to index the aligned read.

#!/bin/bash -l
#SBATCH --partition=angsd_class
#SBATCH --nodes=1
#SBATCH --ntasks=1
#SBATCH --job-name="align-fastqc"
#SBATCH --time=10:0:00 # HH/MM/SS
#SBATCH --mem=40G # memory requested, units available: K,M,G,T
#SBATCH --mail-user=yuc4017@med.cornell.edu
#SBATCH --mail-type=ALL
#SBATCH --requeue

mamba activate angsd

fastqc -o /athena/angsd/scratch/yuc4017/fastqc "/athena/angsd/scratch/yuc4017/fastq/SRR7093809.fastq.gz" --extract

STAR --runMode alignReads \
  --runThreadN 1 \
  --genomeDir /athena/angsd/scratch/yuc4017/genome/index \
  --readFilesIn /athena/angsd/scratch/yuc4017/fastq/SRR7093809.fastq.gz \
  --readFilesCommand zcat \
  --outFileNamePrefix /athena/angsd/scratch/yuc4017/alignments/SRR7093809. \
  --outSAMtype BAM SortedByCoordinate

samtools index /athena/angsd/scratch/yuc4017/alignments/SRR7093809.Aligned.sortedByCoord.out.bam

Fig. 1. FastQC results for Sample SRR7093809: Quality Scores, Sequence Content, GC Distribution

Ran multiqc and bamqc on the aligned read. There were 93.9% uniquely mapped aligned reads. There are 5.7% mapped to multiple loci, 0.1% mapped to too many loci and 0.3% unmapped due to read being too short. The alignment was successful.

V. Download and Align All Samples

Will use a bash script to download the remaining 29 samples and fastqc each. Then, the script will STAR align each sample to the indexed reference genome. I havent run the bash scrip yet to save resources for now (and Im also wondering if I should download each sample into different folders for each sample type: young, old, HGPS).

#!/bin/bash -l
#SBATCH --partition=angsd_class
#SBATCH --nodes=1
#SBATCH --ntasks=1
#SBATCH --job-name="download"
#SBATCH --time=7:0:00 # HH/MM/SS
#SBATCH --mem=50G # memory requested, units available: K,M,G,T
#SBATCH --mail-user=yuc4017@med.cornell.edu
#SBATCH --mail-type=ALL
#SBATCH --requeue
#SBATCH --output=/home/yuc4017/slurm/slurm-%j.out

IFS=" "
SRR_IDS=$(cat SRR_accession_IDs.txt)
read -a SRR_IDS <<< $(cat SRR_accession_IDs.txt)

mamba activate angsd

for ID in "${SRR_IDS[@]}"; do
        echo "==================================="
        echo "Now downloading sample ${ID}"
        if [ ! -r  /athena/angsd/scratch/yuc4017/fastq/${ID}.fastq.gz ]; then
                url="ftp://ftp.sra.ebi.ac.uk/vol1/fastq/SRR709/00${ID: -1}/${ID}/${ID}.fastq.gz"
                echo $url
                curl -L $url -o /athena/angsd/scratch/yuc4017/fastq/${ID}.fastq.gz
        fi
done

for file in /athena/angsd/scratch/yuc4017/fastq/*.fastq.gz; do
        echo "==================================="
        ID=`echo $file | egrep -o 'SRR[0-9]*'`
        echo "FastQC on ${ID}"
        if [ ! -r  /athena/angsd/scratch/yuc4017/fastqc/${ID}_fastqc.html ]; then
                fastqc -o /athena/angsd/scratch/yuc4017/fastqc/ "$file" --extract;
                echo  "/athena/angsd/scratch/yuc4017/fastqc/${ID}_fastqc.html"
        fi
        echo "==================================="
        echo "Alignment on ${ID}"
        if [ ! -r  /athena/angsd/scratch/yuc4017/alignments/${ID}.Log.final.out ]; then
                STAR --runMode alignReads \
                        --runThreadN 1 \
                        --alignIntronMin 1\
                        --alignIntronMax 1300000\
                        --genomeDir /athena/angsd/scratch/yuc4017/genome/index \
                        --readFilesIn /athena/angsd/scratch/yuc4017/fastq/${ID}.fastq.gz \
                        --readFilesCommand zcat \
                        --outFileNamePrefix /athena/angsd/scratch/yuc4017/alignments/${ID}. \
                        --outSAMtype BAM SortedByCoordinate

                samtools index /athena/angsd/scratch/yuc4017/alignments/${ID}.Aligned.sortedByCoord.out.bam
                echo  "/athena/angsd/scratch/yuc4017/alignments/${ID}.Aligned.sortedByCoord.out.bam.bai"
        fi
done
multiqc -o /athena/angsd/scratch/yuc4017/multiqc/all_fastqc/ /athena/angsd/scratch/yuc4017/fastqc/
scp yuc4017@aphrodite.med.cornell.edu:/athena/angsd/scratch/yuc4017/multiqc/all_fastqc/multiqc_report.html .
